Panyam' Painzonnam

Anklets on the feet

Type: Deknni

Source: José Pereira/ Micael Martins. A Sheaf of Deknnis, 

Musical form: Binary

Literary form: Ethnological aspects

Translated by José Pereira


'''Panyam' painzonnam,'''

Anklets on the feet,

Nakako notem.

A ring on the nose.

Sor' sor' sor' kon-nak' bai,

Don't make that scraping noise (so, sor, sor) on the ground, my dear lady.

Panyanchem karhi (kaddi) zotem.

Take your sandals off.



Ailol' Kuxttoba

Kuxttoba had come



